Hi @sdszhang , do you mind to help check if we have any test cases where different neighbors with different ASNs but advertising the same route? I am worried in this case ECMP might not work....
essentially, all return traffic will go to 1 single port on the s4.

> Hi @sdszhang , do you mind to help check if we have any test cases where different neighbors with different ASNs but advertising the same route? I am worried in this case ECMP might not work....

I will check if any test cases in ECMP or BGP for this scenario. Let me know if there is anything else I should check.

> > Hi @sdszhang , do you mind to help check if we have any test cases where different neighbors with different ASNs but advertising the same route? I am worried in this case ECMP might not work....
> 
> I will check if any test cases in ECMP or BGP for this scenario. Let me know if there is anything else I should check.

as discuss in today's meeting, may need to add new test case which needs further investigation. not in this PR.
